Take your measurements using measuring tape, including your bust, waist, and hips. Lay the T-shirt flat and measure it at each of the appropriate areas. Measure half the distance of your measurements (since you are only measuring one side), add at least ½ inch (1.25 cm), and mark it in chalk. Connect these measurements with straight lines. Measure the length from your shoulders to the desired length of your dress, and use this measurement to outline the end of the dress. Finally, repeat these steps for the opposite side of the shirt. Add up to 2 inches (5 cm) for a looser fit. Add extra width at the base if you want the dress to flare. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/be/Make-a-No-Sew-Dress-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-No-Sew-Dress-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/be/Make-a-No-Sew-Dress-Step-2Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-No-Sew-Dress-Step-2Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
